705253f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Troy Avenue
705253f-a.text:
4419 Kings Highway, west side, 50 vards north of Troy Avenue,
showing the John A. Voorhis House, the central portion of which
was built in 1800; the right part was built in 1850. John Voorhis
was Supervisor of the town of Flatlands and Assemblyman from Kings
County.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection 1922
MAY BE REPRODUCED

707091f-a.title: Brooklyn: Troy Ave. - Kings Hwy.
707091f-a.text:
Troy Ave., near King's Highway and westward towards the Flatlands
Dutch Reformed Church, whose spire may be seen beyond the trees. Once, s
brook, known as Van Mater's Skating Pond ran easterly through the Willow
trees seen in the foregroundf.
1922.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
